# Acceptance Testing

## Scope
- Test complete business workflows end-to-end through the API
- Verify correct HTTP status codes, response bodies, and side effects
- Test authentication and authorization flows
- Cover both happy path and error scenarios

## Approach
- Full application context with real (or containerized) dependencies
- All external services stubbed or containerized
- Test from the API consumer's perspective

## Organization
- Group by feature/domain, not by endpoint
- Each test class covers a complete feature scenario
- Clean database state before each test

## Naming
- `*AcceptanceTest.java` or `*AT.java`
- Run separately from unit and integration tests

